reviews.review_text: Quality went down in terms of Food. No longer tasty due to less spicy. I don't why they reduced spice. They increase cost for not worth anymore food taste. Parking space as usual not available. Two wheeler only recommended.

Just good old Goan meals. Family run restaurant. Don't expect too much about decor, ambience, cutlery, music, fancy seating.
The vibe is going to be about beer and cold drink crates lying around, a few dogs loitering around, wooden benches and tables, asbestos roofing, dim lighting and zero views. Just focus on the meals and gupshup. This is a typical small time family Goan eatery setup, a popular local haunt. The restaurant is literally in the family bungalow frontyard! Street parking is ample.
Service is quick, quantity is huge and meals are fresh and delicious. That's all that matters here.
Try their fresh fish Rawa fry, local fish is a favourite here like Chonak, Modso, Tamso, Mandke, Veliyo.
We paid Rs.1400 for a huge crispy rawa fried Modso plate and rawa fried Squid Mandke for two people, which is on the higher side, but it was absolutely yum. Have been visiting this place for past eight years. They have gradually increased their prices, used to be a budget place. There was so much food left, I had to parcel it up.

Lovely little place on the road from dabolim airport to panjim. Absolutely family run and modest setting but nothing modest about the tasty food. The curry is flavourful and spicy. The seafood fresh and generous. My find in the latest trip to goa. The chonak the modso were fresh and tasty but the prawns, the prawns are big and the fried prawn portion is more than generous.
